# Core Universal Rules

## Code Quality (All Files)
- Files MUST be under 500 lines (split if larger)
- Only modify code directly relevant to the request
- Never use placeholders like "// ... rest of code"
- Always complete functions - no partial implementations

## Programming Patterns
- Functional programming preferred, avoid classes
- Descriptive names with auxiliaries (isLoading, hasError)
- Throw errors explicitly, no silent failures
- Add @fileoverview JSDoc to every file

## AI Interaction
- Ask 3-5 clarifying questions ONLY when truly ambiguous
- Otherwise proceed with implementation
- Reference existing patterns before creating new ones
- Check similar components/functions first

